                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/11–1054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-11-11T13:33:00-05:00"
                            >November 11, 1954—1:33 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 92. Re membership (<gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 216). While we are surprised over your
                    estimate re lack of support for Australian joint draft resolution and for our
                    amendment on Vietnam and <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>, we concur in
                    course of action outlined reftel which US Delegation intends follow.</p>
                <p>We strongly hope Committee will not refer Soviet package proposal to <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, since this would weaken <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss>’s past position in opposition to this proposal. Therefore we
                    agree that if resolutions other than Indian-Latin American draft are not voted
                    upon, it would be preferable for Committee not to refer them to <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> after adoption Indian-Latin American draft and to
                    decide no further action necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
